text: i joined aws as a cloud support
associate via the premium support
graduate program here i was able to
apply a lot of the concepts i learned
during my master's program while working
with real-world customer use cases over
the past four years i've been able to
successfully progress my career at aws
today i'm an aws cloud support engineer
working with customers based on around
the world ranging from large enterprises
to startups all with different kinds of
workloads running or getting migrated to
aws the cloud support engineer role
requires a balance between technical and
soft skills from a technical skills
perspective you have to have a good
background in os and networking as a
baseline the amazon leadership principle
learn and be curious is one of the key
soft skills
i have always been a people person
so having the opportunity to work with
amazing colleagues from different
countries and diverse backgrounds has
definitely improved my communication
skills and also helped broaden my
outlook on life i'm involved to the
ireland chapter of the black employee
network ben ie a local affinity group
set up in 2020 the primary role of nie
is to help provide structure and support
for black employees in amazon ireland
play a role in educating amazonians in
ireland and black culture
the most exciting part of my job is
being able to add value to customers
report experience simply knowing that
you just help make a significant
difference to your customer big or small
gives me a great feeling of satisfaction
